messages.message: ok, kinda an oddball question, this might be an @Ashish one but wanna throw it out - inside jypter notebook, do we do anything about tweaking python's memory limits? Basically someone is asking about what the max size of a panda dataframe inside IB as their local limit seems different.
i think they can use a max of 2.14GB memory, so their dataframe should be at least less than that. @Ashish feel free to CMIIW.
